The '''North Carolina United States Senate election of 1968''' was held on 5 November 1968 as part of the [[United States Senate elections, 1968|nation-wide elections to the Senate]].  The general election was fought between the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] incumbent [[Sam Ervin]] and the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] nominee [[Robert Somers]].  Ervin won re-election to a third full term, with over 60% of the vote.

